Full Stack Development refers to the end-to-end development of web applications, covering both the front-end (client side) and back-end (server side) of a project. A Full Stack Developer is capable of working with databases, servers, system engineering, and clients â€” essentially handling an entire applicationâ€™s development workflow.

ğŸ¨ Front-End Development
The front-end is the part of a website or application users interact with directly. It involves creating the layout, design, and interactivity of a web page using:

HTML (HyperText Markup Language) â€” structure of the web pages.

CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) â€” styling and layout.

JavaScript â€” interactivity and dynamic content.

Front-End Frameworks/Libraries:

React.js

Vue.js

